UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Antonio SOTO, Defendant-Appellant. No. 10-15373

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. July 11, 2011. Patricia D. Barksdale, Julie Hackenberry Saveli, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Jacksonville, FL, Robert E. O’Neill, David Paul Rhodes, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Tampa, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Lisa Call, Donna Lee Elm, Federal Public Defender’s Office, Jacksonville, FL, for Defendant-Appellant. Antonio Soto, Big Spring, TX, pro se. *839Before HULL, PRYOR and FAY, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Lisa Call, appointed counsel for Antonio Soto in this direct criminal appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the entire record reveals that counsel’s assessment of the relative merit of the appeal is correct. Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Soto’s conviction and sentence are AFFIRMED.
